{"key":"processedPost-9466052","value":{"id":9466052,"first":9464188,"last":9488263,"when":1229788364,"utime":"12/20/08 05:52 PM","content":"First of all, think in terms of <i>best</i>, not <i>cheapest</i>, because cheap is never best.<br /><br />The light can come in from the sides.&nbsp; If you're worried about crooked fruits for some reason, simply rotate the trays every day or two.&nbsp; Another method is to use small fluorescent fixtures near each tub rather than one large one, as you see from an old pic of one of my mini greenhouses below.&nbsp; However, it's easier to hang a larger fixture from one end and just let it dangle there.&nbsp; It's all good.&nbsp; As long as you have nice bright light, it really doesn't matter how you do it.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/08-51/978825597-Greenhouse_001.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/08-51/978825597-thumb_Greenhouse_001.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: Cheapest way to light a bunch of stacked monotubs???"}}